cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition tasks and proposes a novel network architecture for the same. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech data. Additionally, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new network architecture and uses training criteria to achieve better results. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) as it deals with speech recognition and proposes a new approach to improve the performance.
